<font size=-1><i>All for sh*ts 'n giggles</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utobyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tobyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/01 11:34:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Brittle Haste</span><hr size=1> Always been interested to see how it would work with a DS heavy tank for large scale battles.  Tanks can regularly get DSs up to the 115ish range with mage shield, shaman potion, bard song, coe, etc.  We parsed Lend as doing 20k to herself in one fight just swinging at the tank.  Tack 25% on to her speed and the DS just got alot nastier.  Just have to up the CH chain a bit so it only works if you have some extra healing power.  Could try it on other mobs who are more melee heavy such as Dain.  I imagine you could get him up to 30k dmg on just a DS.<br>
<br>
